00:40.368 --> 00:58.050
handball with the athletic director at Clemson in 
the summer before, I guess it was the summer of 72.

00:58.418 --> 01:02.607
saw where the Aggies were going to come to Clemson 
University for the first time ever. And Clemson

01:03.397 --> 01:06.601
was still a high school football team. They were a 
powerhouse of a basketball program, but their

01:06.621 --> 01:13.229
football program was sophomoreish. And the 
Aggies, by 72, had a heck of a program. And so, man,

01:17.214 --> 01:20.678
the Aggies were coming to Clemson. And we were on 
the East Coast there, so I told athletic director,

01:20.998 --> 01:32.172
if you can get me 50 tickets that I can buy together 
on the 50-yard line, I'll get 50 Aggies there. When

01:32.607 --> 01:34.229
it was all said and done, we had 1,500. The band 
didn't come, but the Rioliers came and Dr.

01:34.309 --> 01:43.220
Williams came because he had been from Clemson. 
And all of a sudden, I think he figured out that he's

01:43.280 --> 01:53.933
got 1,500 Aggies coming from Washington, D.C. to 
Florida and all the Carolinas and Georgia. And he

01:54.915 --> 01:59.340
can go back to his old school and he can kill... 
several birds with one stone. So he came and we had a

02:01.314 --> 02:04.459
big barbecue the night before. And then we had the, 
you know, all the activities, had yellow practice

02:05.260 --> 02:10.367
before the game. And we beat Clemson so bad it was, 
matter of fact, I was kind of proud of the Aggies.

02:16.596 --> 02:26.311
