03:27.464 --> 03:33.630
your notes. Then the last question. Yes, sir. What 
feelings do you carry in your heart for Texas A&M

03:36.273 --> 03:39.817
now?

03:44.321 --> 03:52.369
At 56, and I just turned 56 last month, and now I'm 
back here, and I'm interacting again with old

03:53.547 --> 03:56.030
friends. Oh, I forgot to talk about Buck Wires, but 
Buck was a good friend of mine. I mean, and I dated

04:01.035 --> 04:03.057
his daughter. It was one of the few ladies that I 
would date, and I don't think we were ever going to

04:03.077 --> 04:14.288
be in love, but we were good friends. And then I got 
to know Buck through his daughter, and he was

04:14.509 --> 04:18.913
special. But I think being back and everything 
here, I went back to Houston after being gone for

04:19.636 --> 04:33.190
37, 38 years, and I was not at home. I stayed there 
three months. I was in my old stomping grounds.

04:40.317 --> 04:41.498
That's where we got our apartment. And Jeannie and 
I were just not comfortable. We came up here and we

04:45.202 --> 04:47.905
moved to College Station. And it has been coming 
home. And so in my heart, I've lived all over the

04:52.028 --> 04:56.674
world. I've been to 63 countries at least once, and 
I've been to several of them a dozen times. And I

05:05.044 --> 05:08.168
come back to Texas A&M, and I've come back home. And 
that's a feeling. that you can only get if you've

05:10.733 --> 05:17.656
been all around the world for most of your adult 
life and done all the things I've done. And it's a

05:17.696 --> 05:22.110
very comforting feeling. I've gotten to know Dr. 
Bowen, and I'm so inspired from all the things he's

05:22.917 --> 05:32.367
had to do and his handling of the bonfire. I thought 
it was such world-class handling of such a

05:33.048 --> 05:38.214
traumatic event. When you send your kids to the 
military, you know there's a chance they'll die in

05:38.754 --> 05:47.044
combat, but when you send them to college, you 
don't think they're going to die. And I've been

05:47.945 --> 05:51.068
very impressed with how he and the leadership has 
handled something that I thought was, you know,

05:51.925 --> 05:57.091
one of the great tragedies of all universities. 
So, no, it's hard to describe, and I don't do an

05:58.032 --> 06:20.599
adequate job of articulating really personal 
feelings, but it is, I think it capsulates it when I

05:58.032 --> 06:20.599
say, when we came back to A&M to live, and Jeannie 
says, the next move is to the cemetery. This is our

06:21.895 --> 06:28.090
27th home, and we feel like we're at home. We're 
with friends. We're in an unbelievable comfort

06:30.335 --> 06:33.562
zone here. That's a great ending.

